-- Sulzer Signs $547 Million Revolving Credit Facility to Refinance
-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 2012-04-17T11:05:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/sulzer-signs-547-million-revolving-credit-facility-to-refinance.html
Sulzer AG (SUN) , a Swiss maker of pumps,
signed a 500 million Swiss franc ($547 million) revolving credit
facility to refinance an existing line.  The five-year loan partly replaces a 700 million franc
facility due to mature in August, according to an e-mailed
statement from Citigroup Inc., which coordinated the club-style
deal. Bank of America Merrill Lynch,  Banque Cantonale Vaudoise (BCVN) ,
 Basler Kantonalbank (BSKP) , Credit Suisse Group AG, Deutsche Bank AG,
HSBC Holdings Plc,  Nordea Bank AB (NDA) , UBS AG and Zurcher
Kantonalbank also participated in the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Morris in London at 
 smorris39@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net  